{"questionId":"9067482","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Copper forms two chlorides, copper(I) chloride and copper(II) chloride.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Copper(I) chloride undergoes a disproportionation reaction, producing copper(II) chloride and copper.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">2Cu<sup>+</sup> (aq) → Cu (s) + Cu<sup>2+</sup> (aq)</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Comment on the spontaneity of the disproportionation reaction at 298 K.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">spontaneous <em><strong>AND</strong> E</em><sup>θ</sup> positive ✔</span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067482","referenceCode":"19N.2.hl.TZ0.6e(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Comment on the spontaneity of the disproportionation reaction at 298 K.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"e(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 19: Redox processes","19.1 Electrochemical cells","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 19: Redox processes"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}